"Abstract The growth in the use of the Internet to conduct business has been one of the greatest success stories of the technology age. IT has changed the way organizations do business. Increased Internet usage, combined with related advances in broadband and wireless connectivity, has allowed organizations to open their corporate networks and applications to a wide range of internal and external users. Extranets have, for example, enabled companies to source products more cheaply and efficiently. Many companies have already realised huge benefits from embracing these new technologies, many more will do so in the future. Richard Walters explores the issues and what the corporate response should be."
